<h4> <span style="font-weight: bold;"> Stats 5: Seminar in Data Science, Winter 2017 </span></h4> 

<p>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"> Time: </span> Tuesdays, 11 to 11:50am <br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"> Location: </span> DBH 1300 <br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"> Instructor: </span>  
<a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~smyth">Professor Padhraic Smyth</a><br>
</p>

<p>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"> Description: </span> 
This is a weekly seminar class intended as an introduction to the field of Data Science. 
The course is required for Data Science majors and is also open to other students interested in 
learning about the field and the major.   <br>
</p>

<p>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"> Format: </span> 
Each week will consist of a guest lecture followed by discussion
 on a particular topic related to Data Science, 
with lectures from faculty experts in areas such as statistics, computer science, 
climate science, physics, social science, and more. To pass this class you need to attend
 and submit weekly reports for at least 7 of the 8 guest lectures.<br>
</p>

<p>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"> Grading: </span> Pass/Fail <br>
</p>

<p>  <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~smyth/courses/stats5/onlineslides">
<b> Online copies of lecture slides </b> </a>  <br>
</p>

<p>  <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~smyth/courses/stats5/Forms">
<b> Copies of weekly report templates  </b> </a> (to be submitted each week to EEE dropbox by noon on the day of class)   <br>
</p>

